HEADWORD: Pulverulent
<hw>Pul*ver"u*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pulverulentus</ets>, fr. <ets>pulvis</ets>, <ets>pulveris</ets>,
dust, powder: cf. F. <ets>pulv⟦eacute⟧rulent</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Consisting of, or reducible to, fine powder; covered with dust or
